<p>Minister Isah Zareh Pour stated on Wednesday that authorities would primarily target “exam areas” rather than imposing a nation-scale mobile data ban. The geographic extent of Thursday’s disruption could not be independently corroborated.</p>
<p>NetBlocks recommends against the use of internet shutdowns to prevent cheating in school exams due to their disproportionate impact on the wider community and digital economy.</p>
